'''Landscript''' is a word created by architect [[Seung H-Sang]] to describe his [[Architecture|architecture]]. He published a book with this word as well. In that book, he describes it as follows: 
{{Quote|Like our [[Fingerprint|fingerprints]] and the lines in our palms, the memory of the past remains imprinted on all [[Land|land]]. As every fingerprint is unique, so is the [[Pattern|pattern]] of every piece of land. Sometimes its pattern is created from [[Natural history|natural history]]; sometimes it is a pattern imprinted through the continuity of human life. The record and story of our lives are written on the land. The land is thus a grand and noble book of [[History|history]], and thus is as precious as precious can be. Let us call this the landscript. |author=[[Seung H-Sang]] |source=[http://youlhwadang.co.kr/english/ Youlhwadang Landscript: The Inscription of Nature and Life on the Land]<!-- [http://youlhwadang.co.kr/en/landscript-the-inscription-of-nature-and-life-on-the-land/ (same domain) --> <!-- Need to determine which one is better URL. -->] }}

