{{Infobox language |name= Nangalami |nativename=Grangali |states= [[Afghanistan]] |region= |speakers= 5,000, incl. [[Zemiaki language|Zemiaki]] |date=1994 |ref=e18 |familycolor= Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=[[Dardic languages|Dardic]] |fam5=[[Kunar languages|Kunar]] |dia2=Nangalami (Ningalami) [extinct] |dia1=Grangali |iso3= nli |glotto=gran1245 |glottorefname=Grangali |notice=Indic }}
'''Nangalami''', or '''Grangali''', is a [[Dardic languages|Dardic]] language of [[Afghanistan]]. [[Zemiaki language|Zemiaki]] was formerly considered a Nangalami dialect, but has been reassessed and placed in the [[Nuristani languages|Nuristani]] language group.
