{{Infobox language |name=Vangunu |states=[[Solomon Islands]] |region=[[Vangunu Island]] |speakers=910 |date=1999 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Northwest Solomonic languages|Northwest Solomonic]] |fam5=New Georgia – Ysabel |fam6=[[New Georgia languages|New Georgia]] |iso3=mpr |glotto=vang1243 |glottorefname=Vangunu }}
'''Vangunu''' is an [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic language]] spoken by about 900 people on [[Vangunu Island]], [[Solomon Islands]]. Speakers of Vangunu also use the closely related [[Marovo language|Marovo]].
