{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox settlement |name = Yuzhne |native_name = Южне |settlement_type = [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|City of regional significance]] |image_skyline =File:Yuzhny - Grygorivskogo desantu street.jpg |image_caption = |image_shield = File:Coat of Arms of Yuzhne.png |image_flag = File:Yuzhne prapor.png |shield_size = |pushpin_map =Ukraine Odessa Oblast#Ukraine |pushpin_map1 =Ukraine |pushpin_mapsize = |pushpin_map_caption =Location in Ukraine |subdivision_type =Country |subdivision_name ={{UKR}} |subdivision_type1 =[[Oblasts of Ukraine|Oblast]] |subdivision_name1 ={{flag|Odessa Oblast}} |subdivision_type2 =[[Municipalities of Ukraine|Municipality]] |subdivision_name2 =Yuzhne |population_as_of =2015 |population_total =32003 |area_total_km2 = |elevation_m =34 |blank_name = [[Köppen climate classification|Climate]] |blank_info = [[Humid subtropical climate|Cfa]] | population_footnotes = |timezone =EET |utc_offset =+2 |timezone_DST =EEST |utc_offset_DST =+3 |coordinates = {{coord|46|37|25|N|31|06|04|E|region:UA|display=inline}} |postal_code_type =Postal code |postal_code =65481—65489 |area_code =+380-4842 |website =http://www.yuzhny.org/ }} '''Yuzhne''' ({{lang-uk|Ю́жне}}, formerly: Южний, ''Yuzhny'',<ref>[http://www.yuzhny.org/ Official site of the city]</ref><ref>[http://yuzhny.in.ua/ Information portal of Yuzhny '''Yuzhny on-line''']</ref><ref>[http://www.yuzhny.net/ Telefon directory of Yuzhny]</ref><ref>[http://www.allyuzhny.com/ Description, news, catalog of enterprises of Yuzhny]</ref><ref>[http://www.yuzhny.com/ Internet portal of Yuzhny] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090731121420/http://www.yuzhny.com/ |date=31 July 2009 }}</ref> translated as "southern" [[grammatical gender|n.]] [[adjective|adj.]]) is a port [[city]] in [[Odessa Oblast]] ([[oblast|province]]) of south-western [[Ukraine]]. Administratively, Yuzhne is incorporated as a [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|town of oblast significance]]. It is situated on the country's [[Black Sea]] coast. Population: {{Ua-pop-est2015|32,003}}
Initially created as a settlement of the Odessa Portside Plant in the Hryhorivka Estuary, since 1981 it was transformed into a suburb of Odessa within the Suvorovsky District of the city. From the Southern Marine Terminal of the city port, the [[Odessa–Brody pipeline]] takes its beginning towards the [[Western Ukraine]].
The city's port is an internationally important oil [[Container terminal|terminal]], and one of Ukraine's top three ports, with [[Odessa]] and [[Chornomorsk]]. In fact, these three nearby port cities have grown into a single [[conurbation]], and Yuzhne is considered a satellite of Odessa.
== Name == The city is located about 32 kilometers (20 miles) east of [[Odessa]]. Although it sounds awkwardly in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]], the city's name has not changed since [[Ukraine]] obtained its independence. The correct way to name the town in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] is ''Pivdenne'', rather than ''Yuzhne''. [[File:Olimp Sports Complex in Yuzhne.jpg|thumb|left|Olimp Sports Complex in Yuzhne]] Nonetheless, on 11 May 1978 by the order of the Presidium of [[Verkhovna Rada]] of [[Ukrainian SSR]] the newly built populated place was given the name of the village Yuzhne. Starting from this event the place takes its beginning. In February 1993 the [[Verkhovna Rada]] of [[Ukraine]] declared to give the urbanized village a special status in the [[Odessa Oblast]] as a [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|city of oblast significance]]. In 2000 the declaration of [[Verkhovna Rada]] #1914-III confirmed the city limits.
== Climate == Yuzhne has a [[humid subtropical climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification|Köppen]]: ''Cfa''). [[File:Yuzhny - beach.jpg|thumb|left|Yuzhny beach]] {{Weather box |location = Yuzhne |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan mean C = -1.9 |Feb mean C = -1.1 |Mar mean C = 2.5 |Apr mean C = 9.4 |May mean C = 15.5 |Jun mean C = 20.0 |Jul mean C = 22.3 |Aug mean C = 21.7 |Sep mean C = 16.9 |Oct mean C = 11.1 |Nov mean C = 5.3 |Dec mean C = 1.1 |year mean C = 10.2 |Jan precipitation mm = 36 |Feb precipitation mm = 37 |Mar precipitation mm = 29 |Apr precipitation mm = 32 |May precipitation mm = 39 |Jun precipitation mm = 47 |Jul precipitation mm = 50 |Aug precipitation mm = 36 |Sep precipitation mm = 38 |Oct precipitation mm = 26 |Nov precipitation mm = 39 |Dec precipitation mm = 43 |year precipitation mm = |source 1 = Climate-Data.org<ref name="Climate-Data.org">{{cite web|url=http://en.climate-data.org/location/705914/ |title = Climate: Yuzhne |accessdate = 4 May 2014 |publisher = Climate-Data.org}}</ref> }}
== Sport == Yuzhne is home to the team [[BC Khimik]] in the [[Ukrainian Basketball Superleague]], league champions in the 2014/15 season. Yuzhne is also home to the "BK Khimik" women's volleyball team, Ukrainian champions in 2010/11 and 2011/12. The handball team named HC Portovik plays in the highest men's League.
